1
00:00:02,535 --> 00:00:05,904
      Cutie Mark Crusaders!
      Cutie Mark Crusaders!

2
00:00:06,206 --> 00:00:07,706
      Cutie Mark Crusaders!

3
00:00:07,908 --> 00:00:09,341
      Cutie Mark Crusaders!

4
00:00:09,443 --> 00:00:11,176
  Scootaloo: We're at my house!

5
00:00:12,646 --> 00:00:14,746
      I got my cutie mark!

6
00:00:14,848 --> 00:00:15,847
                        You did?

7
00:00:16,049 --> 00:00:17,616
    That's great, Skeedaddle!

8
00:00:17,818 --> 00:00:19,385
      Yeah! What's it for?

9
00:00:19,587 --> 00:00:20,920
           Knot tying!

10
00:00:21,022 --> 00:00:23,322
   And I never would've gotten
   it without all of you!

11
00:00:23,524 --> 00:00:25,491
                  Did we suggest
                  knot-tying?

12
00:00:26,193 --> 00:00:28,360
         First, I tried sailing,
          like you said.

13
00:00:28,662 --> 00:00:31,030
     Next, I tried fishing,
     like YOU said.

14
00:00:31,132 --> 00:00:34,633
   Then I tried rowing, like
   you said. But my oar broke.

15
00:00:34,735 --> 00:00:37,136
   So I used my fishing line
   to tie it back together...

16
00:00:37,238 --> 00:00:39,104
    AND I GOT MY CUTIE MARK!

17
00:00:39,206 --> 00:00:41,406
AHH! I can't wait to tell EVERYPONY!

18
00:00:43,043 --> 00:00:43,675
          [door closes]

19
00:00:43,777 --> 00:00:44,744
               Yay!
   Yeah!
                       Woohoo!

20
00:00:44,846 --> 00:00:47,012
       [Australian accent]
       Oh, how exciting!

21
00:00:47,114 --> 00:00:50,649
   You three truly have a
    gift for helping ponies.

22
00:00:50,751 --> 00:00:52,451
    Aw, thanks, Aunt Holiday.

23
00:00:52,553 --> 00:00:54,954
    But I'm not sure we can
    take credit for this one.

24
00:00:55,256 --> 00:00:56,555
       Of course, you can!

25
00:00:56,657 --> 00:00:58,690
    You encouraged that
     colt to try new things.

26
00:00:58,792 --> 00:01:01,761
  And because you all believed
   in him, he succeeded.

27
00:01:02,663 --> 00:01:04,896
 I could use that kind of help... Hmph.

28
00:01:05,399 --> 00:01:06,417
      [laugh]

29
00:01:06,518 --> 00:01:10,236
   C'mon, Auntie Lofty. You
  already HAVE your cutie mark.

30
00:01:10,738 --> 00:01:12,404
     Lot of good it does me.

31
00:01:12,906 --> 00:01:15,707
     I can't decide what
    theme to give this quilt.

32
00:01:15,809 --> 00:01:17,643
 Ah. I've run out of inspiration.

33
00:01:17,745 --> 00:01:20,179
        How about apples?
        Puppies? Kites!

34
00:01:20,381 --> 00:01:22,247
   Or cotton candy? Or ballet!

35
00:01:22,349 --> 00:01:23,782
 What about a Wonderbolt quilt?

36
00:01:23,884 --> 00:01:26,085
        Ha ha! See? Leave
         it to you three

37
00:01:26,187 --> 00:01:28,820
   to come up with more ideas
   than I've had in a year.

38
00:01:28,922 --> 00:01:30,556
       Now that's talent!

39
00:01:30,758 --> 00:01:33,492
            [cuckoos]

40
00:01:33,594 --> 00:01:34,960
 Goodness, we'd better get going

41
00:01:35,062 --> 00:01:36,495
  or we'll miss our train home.

42
00:01:36,597 --> 00:01:39,498
  I left you plenty of healthy
   food for the weekend.

43
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:41,767
     And <i>I</i> left you cookies. Heh.

44
00:01:41,869 --> 00:01:42,702
         [excited gasps]

45
00:01:43,204 --> 00:01:45,904
    The Cakes will stay with
    you tonight, then Rarity,

46
00:01:46,006 --> 00:01:47,906
  and Rainbow Dash after that.

47
00:01:48,108 --> 00:01:50,241
    Remember, we're just a
    few stops from Ponyville

48
00:01:50,343 --> 00:01:51,076
         if you need us.

49
00:01:51,178 --> 00:01:53,813
     She knows, Holiday! See
     you next week, slugger.

50
00:01:54,615 --> 00:01:57,649
       Bye, Aunt Holiday!
       Bye, Auntie Lofty!

51
00:01:57,751 --> 00:01:58,283
          [door closes]

52
00:01:58,485 --> 00:02:00,719
     Your aunts are so nice!

53
00:02:00,921 --> 00:02:02,888
        Yeah! It's really
       cool they watch you

54
00:02:02,990 --> 00:02:04,523
  while your parents are gone.

55
00:02:04,625 --> 00:02:07,526
       I know! I just wish
       they lived closer.

56
00:02:07,728 --> 00:02:10,095
 Nopony bakes like Auntie Lofty..

57
00:02:10,197 --> 00:02:10,963
         [knock at door]

58
00:02:11,843 --> 00:02:12,643
          [door opens]

59
00:02:13,968 --> 00:02:16,702
   [gasp] They're coming home today!

60
00:02:16,904 --> 00:02:17,503
      Who?

61
00:02:17,605 --> 00:02:19,537
           MY PARENTS!

62
00:02:59,480 --> 00:03:00,712
        Today we're going to learn

63
00:03:00,814 --> 00:03:03,115
        about the Pegasus
        Weather Factory.

64
00:03:03,717 --> 00:03:06,518
        Once everypony is
         in their seats...

65
00:03:06,620 --> 00:03:07,286
          [door closes]

66
00:03:10,291 --> 00:03:14,393
  The factory specializes in
  snow, rain, sunshine, and...

67
00:03:14,795 --> 00:03:17,797
      Ahem! Scootaloo. May
        I help you?

68
00:03:18,199 --> 00:03:21,700
      I.. just noticed your
     erasers needed dusting!

69
00:03:22,102 --> 00:03:23,268
            [tapping]

70
00:03:23,370 --> 00:03:26,872
           [coughing]

71
00:03:26,974 --> 00:03:30,142
  Why don't we hold off on the
  lesson until after lunch?

72
00:03:30,544 --> 00:03:33,879
    How about show and tell?
    Does anypony have any...

73
00:03:33,981 --> 00:03:37,349
    My parents are coming
    home to Ponyville today!!

74
00:03:37,651 --> 00:03:40,652
   Wait. They don't live here?

75
00:03:40,854 --> 00:03:44,090
    Nope. Their jobs are way
     too important for that.

76
00:03:44,492 --> 00:03:47,626
  They travel to the farthest,
  most dangerous places

77
00:03:47,728 --> 00:03:51,663
  in Equestria to study unknown
  plants and fierce creatures.

78
00:03:52,133 --> 00:03:55,334
   And what they learn helps
   pony science and medicine!

79
00:03:55,636 --> 00:03:58,504
      I'd go with them, but
       it's TOO dangerous.

80
00:04:00,307 --> 00:04:03,809
    Once, my mom had to
     wing-wrestle a wyvern!

81
00:04:04,011 --> 00:04:07,012
     And my dad got trapped
      in a chimera's cave

82
00:04:07,114 --> 00:04:11,883
  for three moons! He still
   has the scars to prove it.

83
00:04:12,085 --> 00:04:12,652
             Pffft!

84
00:04:13,154 --> 00:04:16,688
  You're making that up.
  Nopony has THAT kind of job.

85
00:04:16,790 --> 00:04:19,491
           [crashing]

86
00:04:19,593 --> 00:04:22,527
            [roaring]

87
00:04:22,629 --> 00:04:23,628
       [frightened gasps]

88
00:04:23,730 --> 00:04:24,696
         [shrill scream]

89
00:04:24,798 --> 00:04:28,467
           [screaming]

90
00:04:28,569 --> 00:04:30,402
               It's a CRAGADILE!

91
00:04:30,526 --> 00:04:36,426
     <i> ♪ [action music] ♪</i>

92
00:04:36,544 --> 00:04:38,577
    Easy there, Marshmallow!

93
00:04:38,979 --> 00:04:40,913
      Time you were in your
       crate for your nap!

94
00:04:42,061 --> 00:04:44,061
            [growling]

95
00:04:45,686 --> 00:04:47,653
   And that means now, mister!

96
00:04:48,757 --> 00:04:51,056
          [whimpering]

97
00:04:52,727 --> 00:04:53,893
                   [slam]

98
00:04:55,863 --> 00:04:56,595
                   [happy gasp]

99
00:04:56,797 --> 00:04:58,697
            Mom! Dad!

100
00:04:58,799 --> 00:04:59,998
       [delighted squeak]

101
00:05:00,100 --> 00:05:02,268
        Still think she's
        makin' it all up?

102
00:05:03,070 --> 00:05:04,436
             Nuh-uh!

103
00:05:05,639 --> 00:05:11,043
Everypony, meet my parents:
 Snap Shutter and Mane Allgood.

104
00:05:11,645 --> 00:05:13,312
Heh. Sorry to make such an entrance.

105
00:05:13,514 --> 00:05:15,581
  Just brought back a few mates
    from our last adventure.

106
00:05:15,683 --> 00:05:18,717
    We couldn't wait another
    moment to see Scootaloo!

107
00:05:18,919 --> 00:05:20,953
             I hope we didn't
             interrupt anything.

108
00:05:22,356 --> 00:05:25,891
        No, I... think
       class is dismissed.

109
00:05:26,393 --> 00:05:30,062
      [excited chattering]

110
00:05:30,164 --> 00:05:33,298
    Crikey! You're nearly as
     tall as me now, Scoot!

111
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:34,866
                 Aw, c'mon, Dad.

112
00:05:34,968 --> 00:05:37,769
  Oh, Scootaloo. We missed you!

113
00:05:37,871 --> 00:05:41,006
      Me too, Mom! Did you
      get all my letters?

114
00:05:41,308 --> 00:05:43,108
And read them twenty times!

115
00:05:43,210 --> 00:05:45,277
But they're never as
good as the real thing.

116
00:05:45,979 --> 00:05:47,813
    It's so good to see you.

117
00:05:47,915 --> 00:05:51,417
I say we celebrate
with ice cream sundaes!

118
00:05:51,719 --> 00:05:53,919
  They don't have THOSE in the
    jungle, that's for sure.

119
00:05:54,121 --> 00:05:56,187
Why don't you all
come? Our treat!

120
00:06:01,562 --> 00:06:02,828
   And Princess Twilight said

121
00:06:02,930 --> 00:06:04,396
       we're such good
       friendship tutors,

122
00:06:04,498 --> 00:06:06,698
       she might even let
       us TEACH a class!

123
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,099
Good on ya, Scoot!

124
00:06:08,201 --> 00:06:09,268
                  What an honor!

125
00:06:09,970 --> 00:06:12,171
    I can give you a tour of
    the school if you want!

126
00:06:12,273 --> 00:06:14,906
    I mean, if you're staying
     for a while this time.

127
00:06:15,008 --> 00:06:17,542
Oh, you'll be
seeing plenty of us.

128
00:06:18,245 --> 00:06:19,111
             Really!?

129
00:06:19,213 --> 00:06:22,047
   Mm hm. Because we've
   taken a new job assignment

130
00:06:22,149 --> 00:06:24,283
      that will let ALL
      of us live together!

131
00:06:24,585 --> 00:06:28,187
         I can't believe
       it! That's AWESOME!

132
00:06:28,789 --> 00:06:30,356
               All right,
               Scootaloo!

133
00:06:30,580 --> 00:06:31,557
Woo hoo!

134
00:06:31,658 --> 00:06:34,560
 We never planned to be away for
   so long in the first place.

135
00:06:34,762 --> 00:06:36,428
 We just kept discovering things

136
00:06:36,530 --> 00:06:38,964
    that could help
   Equestria, and nopony else

137
00:06:39,066 --> 00:06:41,533
       had the experience
       to finish our job.

138
00:06:41,635 --> 00:06:44,369
  But with all that's happened
   lately: Sombra's return,

139
00:06:44,471 --> 00:06:46,605
     the destruction of
      the Tree of Harmony,

140
00:06:46,707 --> 00:06:49,308
      we decided our family
       should be together.

141
00:06:52,179 --> 00:06:55,280
This is the best day of my life!

142
00:06:55,482 --> 00:06:57,048
              We'll stay in town
              for the weekend

143
00:06:57,150 --> 00:06:58,350
                 so you can pack
                 your things.

144
00:06:58,452 --> 00:06:59,918
          Wait...WHAT?

145
00:07:00,220 --> 00:07:02,354
                We're all moving
                to Shirelanka!

146
00:07:02,656 --> 00:07:03,822
                That's where our
                new job is.

147
00:07:03,924 --> 00:07:06,625
               But...my friends
               are in Ponyville!

148
00:07:07,227 --> 00:07:08,694
        You can come back
        and visit 'em.

149
00:07:08,796 --> 00:07:11,263
  Or they can take the train to
  us. There's one every month.

150
00:07:11,765 --> 00:07:13,565
   But Scootaloo can't leave!

151
00:07:13,667 --> 00:07:15,566
We've been together
our whole lives!

152
00:07:16,237 --> 00:07:18,437
           It'll be a big
           change for everypony.

153
00:07:18,539 --> 00:07:22,241
   But it'll be a good change!
   Give it time; you'll see.

154
00:07:22,343 --> 00:07:23,909
         The only thing I see...

155
00:07:24,211 --> 00:07:28,013
           is the end of the
           Cutie Mark Crusaders!

156
00:07:34,655 --> 00:07:36,121
          [tap tap tap]

157
00:07:36,523 --> 00:07:37,222
             [sniff]

158
00:07:37,324 --> 00:07:39,558
    I now call our last ever

159
00:07:39,660 --> 00:07:42,094
       Cutie Mark Crusader
        meeting to order.

160
00:07:42,396 --> 00:07:46,631
  First item of business, cry!

161
00:07:46,733 --> 00:07:52,103
         [loud wailing]

162
00:07:52,205 --> 00:07:53,973
            [banging]

163
00:07:54,275 --> 00:07:57,876
 You can't let the blank flanks
 down just cause I'm gone.

164
00:07:58,178 --> 00:08:01,613
      You gotta keep being
      CMCs without me!

165
00:08:01,915 --> 00:08:05,618
  [sniff] How!? There's only two of us!

166
00:08:06,420 --> 00:08:09,488
      Maybe you can find
      a replacement for me!

167
00:08:09,590 --> 00:08:13,592
        No, we can't!
      You're the only.. YOU!

168
00:08:13,694 --> 00:08:15,594
   Nothin's gonna be the same!

169
00:08:15,796 --> 00:08:18,964
 Who's gonna ride their scooter
  ahead of us everywhere we go!?

170
00:08:19,066 --> 00:08:21,567
 Or... or put on plays with us!?

171
00:08:21,669 --> 00:08:25,838
    Or go camping with us!? Or
    just...hang out with us!?

172
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:31,376
 Well, it's worse for me! I have
 to say goodbye to BOTH OF-

173
00:08:31,478 --> 00:08:32,311
          [door opens]

174
00:08:32,513 --> 00:08:34,413
      Guess who just got
     three front-row tickets

175
00:08:34,515 --> 00:08:36,014
       to the Wonderbolts
       show next week?

176
00:08:36,216 --> 00:08:41,019
          [blubbering]

177
00:08:41,121 --> 00:08:44,256
     Uh, that is NOT the
    reaction I was expecting.

178
00:08:44,693 --> 00:08:48,827
  [sniffles] Thanks for the tickets,
  Rainbow Dash. But I can't go.

179
00:08:48,929 --> 00:08:50,195
 Her parents are making her move

180
00:08:50,297 --> 00:08:52,497
 super far away from Ponyville!

181
00:08:52,699 --> 00:08:56,335
What!? No way!
Scootaloo belongs HERE!

182
00:08:56,737 --> 00:09:01,907
  And now we'll probably never
  see her again! It's HOPELESS!

183
00:09:02,009 --> 00:09:04,275
            [wailing]

184
00:09:04,377 --> 00:09:05,377
Whoa whoa whoa!

185
00:09:06,079 --> 00:09:09,080
I cannot believe you're
giving up so easily!

186
00:09:09,182 --> 00:09:11,616
You're the Cutie
Mark Crusaders!

187
00:09:11,718 --> 00:09:13,618
Solving tough problems
is what you do!

188
00:09:15,022 --> 00:09:18,423
      We are pretty good at
      coming up with ideas...

189
00:09:18,525 --> 00:09:22,828
That's right! When we work
together, we're unstoppable!

190
00:09:22,930 --> 00:09:25,297
       I can't believe we didn't
       think of it before!

191
00:09:25,399 --> 00:09:27,098
          It's list time, y'all!

192
00:09:29,135 --> 00:09:30,035
         First question,

193
00:09:30,137 --> 00:09:32,571
   why do Scootaloo's parents
   want to move to Shirelanka?

194
00:09:32,873 --> 00:09:34,240
 That's where their new job is.

195
00:09:34,342 --> 00:09:37,943
[gasp] What if we get
them a job HERE instead?

196
00:09:38,145 --> 00:09:40,813
    Yeah! They like dangerous
     creatures, right?

197
00:09:41,315 --> 00:09:43,314
       We gotta have some
      of those around here.

198
00:09:43,416 --> 00:09:45,150
      Like... Timberwolves!

199
00:09:45,452 --> 00:09:48,920
 Dad knows all about those. And
 cockatrices, and bugbears...

200
00:09:49,022 --> 00:09:51,523
They only study
super-rare animals.

201
00:09:51,625 --> 00:09:54,325
Then maybe we need to
give them an animal

202
00:09:54,427 --> 00:09:56,295
nopony's ever heard of!

203
00:09:56,397 --> 00:09:58,964
        Uh.. then how would
        <i>we</i> hear about it?

204
00:09:59,066 --> 00:10:02,000
       Because we're
      making it up! C'mon!

205
00:10:02,102 --> 00:10:04,169
               ♪♪

206
00:10:04,271 --> 00:10:07,472
      So... you want these
      tickets, or...?

207
00:10:07,574 --> 00:10:10,041
               ♪♪

208
00:10:10,143 --> 00:10:12,311
      This is what I
       wanted to show you!

209
00:10:12,413 --> 00:10:17,316
  The tracks of the <i>mysterious</i>
  Everfree Banshee Beast!

210
00:10:17,518 --> 00:10:21,153
      Hmm, they're like
     nothing I've ever seen!

211
00:10:21,455 --> 00:10:25,824
     Legend says it has five
     claws and three wings,

212
00:10:25,926 --> 00:10:29,061
and it's super-dangerous
if you get close.

213
00:10:29,763 --> 00:10:33,298
     If only somepony
     could prove it exists..!

214
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:37,168
Hmm. Easy enough. We'll
follow the spoor.

215
00:10:37,270 --> 00:10:39,306
♪♪

216
00:10:39,430 --> 00:10:41,230
           [Scootaloo whining]

217
00:10:41,308 --> 00:10:43,375
       I think I heard
       something this way!

218
00:10:43,677 --> 00:10:49,548
     <i> ♪ [mysterious music] ♪</i>

219
00:10:49,650 --> 00:10:54,753
            [grunts]

220
00:10:54,855 --> 00:10:56,988
    So the plan is, we
     let 'em get a picture,

221
00:10:57,090 --> 00:10:58,556
   then we hide again, right?

222
00:10:58,660 --> 00:11:00,461
Woah..!        
[shutter clicks]

223
00:11:02,285 --> 00:11:02,985
[shutter clicks]

224
00:11:04,631 --> 00:11:07,366
      Now the plan is.. RUN!

225
00:11:07,768 --> 00:11:10,969
       [panicked panting]

226
00:11:11,071 --> 00:11:12,937
       [stretching sound]

227
00:11:13,039 --> 00:11:14,238
             [snap]
             Whoa!

228
00:11:14,308 --> 00:11:15,274
             [thud]

229
00:11:17,454 --> 00:11:18,054
             [thud]

230
00:11:19,079 --> 00:11:21,914
       Heh-heh. Guess you
       solved the mystery...

231
00:11:22,216 --> 00:11:24,950
    We'd better get back.
   There's a lot to get ready

232
00:11:25,052 --> 00:11:27,085
      before the house goes
      up for sale tomorrow.

233
00:11:27,187 --> 00:11:28,186
             [moan]

234
00:11:32,159 --> 00:11:33,692
     Don't worry, Scootaloo.

235
00:11:33,794 --> 00:11:36,127
      We have a NEW plan to
     keep you in Ponyville.

236
00:11:36,329 --> 00:11:39,197
We just gotta show your
parents we're a set of three!

237
00:11:39,299 --> 00:11:41,599
Then they'll have to let
you stay here with us!

238
00:11:41,923 --> 00:11:42,623
           [camera snap]

239
00:11:55,949 --> 00:11:57,882
     Scoot? Are these yours?

240
00:12:01,154 --> 00:12:02,821
       Yeah! Thanks, Dad.

241
00:12:02,923 --> 00:12:05,024
   We're sending them to
    the Pony Book of Records.

242
00:12:05,426 --> 00:12:07,692
            We're the only three
             ponies in Equestria

243
00:12:07,794 --> 00:12:08,994
                   with the SAME
                    cutie mark!

244
00:12:09,096 --> 00:12:11,196
The chances of that
are so rare,

245
00:12:11,298 --> 00:12:14,300
it means we belong
together, forever!

246
00:12:15,302 --> 00:12:17,636
    Yeah, but you <i>don't</i> have
    the same cutie mark.

247
00:12:18,338 --> 00:12:20,972
      Uh, sure we do! Look!

248
00:12:21,274 --> 00:12:23,742
  Well, this part is the same,
   but the picture inside,

249
00:12:23,844 --> 00:12:25,177
   each of these is different.

250
00:12:25,379 --> 00:12:27,112
     I think it means you'll
       stay best friends,

251
00:12:27,214 --> 00:12:29,748
   no matter where you go.
   And that's really special.

252
00:12:30,450 --> 00:12:34,752
      But...we... How do
      you argue with that?

253
00:12:39,426 --> 00:12:40,592
             [sigh]

254
00:12:40,894 --> 00:12:44,062
   All right, y'all. Time to
    take things up a notch!

255
00:12:47,467 --> 00:12:48,934
        With prune juice?

256
00:12:49,336 --> 00:12:51,670
It's a potion I mixed
up from Zecora's book!

257
00:12:51,972 --> 00:12:54,105
Prune is only ONE
of the ingredients.

258
00:12:54,207 --> 00:12:55,106
                   What's it do?

259
00:12:57,144 --> 00:13:01,346
   On this potion, please
  depend. Any separation, mend.

260
00:13:01,548 --> 00:13:03,682
 Friends together till the end!

261
00:13:03,884 --> 00:13:05,784
We just gotta dab a
little on our hooves.

262
00:13:05,886 --> 00:13:07,418
Sounds perfect, right?

263
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:09,020
      Better than perfect!

264
00:13:10,322 --> 00:13:15,290
               ♪♪

265
00:13:16,063 --> 00:13:17,898
Is something supposed to happen?

266
00:13:18,175 --> 00:13:20,075
  [magic shimmering]

267
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:21,533
             [snap]

268
00:13:21,935 --> 00:13:24,469
    Is THIS the something
   that's supposed to happen!?

269
00:13:24,671 --> 00:13:26,371
The book didn't really say.

270
00:13:26,673 --> 00:13:29,040
              Whoa!

271
00:13:29,142 --> 00:13:29,775
             [crash]

272
00:13:30,177 --> 00:13:31,876
      Thanks for trying,
      Apple Bloom.

273
00:13:31,978 --> 00:13:33,345
         But I might as
          well face it.

274
00:13:33,747 --> 00:13:35,580
      I'm gonna have to
      leave Ponyville.

275
00:13:37,083 --> 00:13:38,850
Don't give up, Scootaloo!

276
00:13:38,952 --> 00:13:40,752
This just gave me
an even BETTER idea

277
00:13:40,854 --> 00:13:43,188
how to keep you
here. C'mon!

278
00:13:43,290 --> 00:13:44,555
              Whoa!

279
00:13:44,657 --> 00:13:45,357
             [thud]

280
00:13:46,059 --> 00:13:49,794
  Maybe we'd better see Zecora
    about fixing this first.

281
00:13:53,667 --> 00:13:54,933
   We're running out of time.

282
00:13:55,135 --> 00:13:59,738
           [clinking]

283
00:13:59,840 --> 00:14:01,539
        This HAS to work!

284
00:14:03,143 --> 00:14:05,844
   Scootaloo? I know you're
  having fun with your friends,

285
00:14:05,946 --> 00:14:08,246
   but we need to get all our
     things to the station.

286
00:14:08,548 --> 00:14:10,248
 We can't miss tomorrow's train.

287
00:14:10,350 --> 00:14:11,850
 It's the only one for a month!

288
00:14:13,820 --> 00:14:15,988
      Then you'll just have
       to go without me!

289
00:14:16,590 --> 00:14:18,890
   I'm staying with the CMCs!

290
00:14:19,292 --> 00:14:21,192
  We are chained to this post!

291
00:14:21,294 --> 00:14:25,029
    And nuthin' and nopony is
   gonna move us, no matter...

292
00:14:25,899 --> 00:14:26,798
              ...what.

293
00:14:31,004 --> 00:14:32,604
 We just sold the house, Scoot.

294
00:14:33,106 --> 00:14:35,239
       I know this is hard
        to accept, but...

295
00:14:35,341 --> 00:14:38,109
       It's more than
      hard! It's NOT FAIR!

296
00:14:38,411 --> 00:14:41,513
  You're making me pick between
   my family and my friends!

297
00:14:41,815 --> 00:14:44,983
    Oh, Scootaloo. Moving
    away won't stop you three

298
00:14:45,085 --> 00:14:47,852
  from caring about each other.
  Why don't you sleep over

299
00:14:47,954 --> 00:14:49,754
     with Sweetie Belle and
      Apple Bloom tonight?

300
00:14:49,856 --> 00:14:52,424
     It'll give you a chance
     to say a real goodbye.

301
00:14:52,726 --> 00:14:55,260
But I don't WANT to say goodbye!

302
00:14:55,962 --> 00:14:57,696
  You're changing my whole life

303
00:14:57,798 --> 00:15:00,732
 without even asking how I FEEL!

304
00:15:00,834 --> 00:15:03,401
          [blubbering]

305
00:15:11,611 --> 00:15:12,544
           Scootaloo!

306
00:15:13,546 --> 00:15:14,746
      Where are you going!?

307
00:15:15,048 --> 00:15:17,749
     To stay with my aunts.
      You heard my parents!

308
00:15:18,151 --> 00:15:20,752
   There isn't another train
   to Shirelanka for a month.

309
00:15:20,954 --> 00:15:23,355
    If I'm not on it, they'll
     have to go without me.

310
00:15:24,557 --> 00:15:26,191
   Then we're comin' with ya!

311
00:15:27,093 --> 00:15:29,861
   Are you sure? I don't want
     to get you in trouble.

312
00:15:29,963 --> 00:15:30,962
      Rarity won't be mad.

313
00:15:31,064 --> 00:15:32,297
       Applejack neither!

314
00:15:32,399 --> 00:15:34,600
     I bet she'd do the same
     thing for her friends.

315
00:15:36,002 --> 00:15:37,669
 You're the best, you know that?

316
00:15:37,971 --> 00:15:39,203
         WE'RE the best.

317
00:15:39,405 --> 00:15:40,438
            Together!

318
00:15:40,540 --> 00:15:43,473
       [train whistles and
         rattles closer]

319
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:48,913
           [knocking]

320
00:15:50,283 --> 00:15:53,652
[gasp] Scootaloo! What a nice surprise!

321
00:15:54,354 --> 00:15:56,588
And I've got a surprise for you!

322
00:15:58,959 --> 00:16:01,860
      You three inspired me
       to finish my quilt.

323
00:16:02,062 --> 00:16:04,729
      See? It's Cutie Mark
      Crusader themed!

324
00:16:04,931 --> 00:16:08,099
  We love hearing stories about
  all the ponies you've helped.

325
00:16:08,201 --> 00:16:11,970
  So Lofty decided to celebrate
  the special job you three do!

326
00:16:12,972 --> 00:16:14,106
             [sigh]

327
00:16:15,008 --> 00:16:17,441
               It's.. still a work
                in progress.

328
00:16:18,879 --> 00:16:21,813
It's not your quilt we're
sad about, Auntie Lofty.

329
00:16:22,115 --> 00:16:23,581
Mom and Dad are back.

330
00:16:23,683 --> 00:16:26,651
And they're making me move
to Shirelanka with them!

331
00:16:27,153 --> 00:16:29,988
Snap and Mane are back?
They didn't tell me that!

332
00:16:30,190 --> 00:16:32,023
        Oh. I think the
       mailpony delivered

333
00:16:32,125 --> 00:16:33,591
    your letter to my house.

334
00:16:37,864 --> 00:16:41,366
I love my family! But I love
being with my friends, too.

335
00:16:41,568 --> 00:16:43,534
 I don't want to have to choose...

336
00:16:43,636 --> 00:16:45,136
              Well then, why
              don't your parents

337
00:16:45,238 --> 00:16:46,571
         just stay in Ponyville?

338
00:16:47,673 --> 00:16:49,774
   Their job is too important...

339
00:16:50,076 --> 00:16:51,109
That's it!

340
00:16:51,311 --> 00:16:53,311
                 Is this another
                 potion idea?

341
00:16:53,413 --> 00:16:57,115
  No! Scootaloo's parents are
  the only ponies in Equestria

342
00:16:57,217 --> 00:16:59,217
that can do what they do, right?

343
00:17:00,019 --> 00:17:00,952
    Right..?

344
00:17:01,254 --> 00:17:05,123
Well, so are we! Our
cutie marks prove it!

345
00:17:05,425 --> 00:17:09,461
 Yeah! Our job is to help other
 ponies find their purpose!

346
00:17:09,963 --> 00:17:13,932
  And nopony else can do that!
 So, if my parents split us up,

347
00:17:14,034 --> 00:17:17,001
     it'd be just as bad as
    them quitting their jobs!

348
00:17:17,103 --> 00:17:18,436
             Woohoo!

349
00:17:18,538 --> 00:17:20,304
           [giggling]

350
00:17:20,406 --> 00:17:22,741
      Now.. how do we
      explain that to 'em?

351
00:17:22,843 --> 00:17:25,643
       Oh, <i>you</i> don't have
         to explain it.

352
00:17:25,945 --> 00:17:27,078
           THEY will.

353
00:17:30,116 --> 00:17:31,916
   Feeling better, Scootaloo?

354
00:17:32,218 --> 00:17:35,654
A little. I just wanna show
you something before we go.

355
00:17:36,056 --> 00:17:39,123
All right, but let's make it
swift. That train won't wait.

356
00:17:43,730 --> 00:17:45,897
                Sweet Celestia's
                 slippers!

357
00:17:45,999 --> 00:17:47,431
     Mane: What is all this?

358
00:17:50,437 --> 00:17:53,104
    It's Cutie Mark Crusader
    Appreciation Day!

359
00:17:53,206 --> 00:17:55,607
    But we couldn't start
    without ALL of them here!

360
00:17:59,446 --> 00:18:08,117
        CMCs! CMCs! CMCs!
        CMCs! CMCs! CMCs!

361
00:18:08,421 --> 00:18:11,222
            These three ponies
            share a rare ability

362
00:18:11,324 --> 00:18:13,858
       to help others find
       their true purpose.

363
00:18:13,960 --> 00:18:17,495
    It's a job only they can
     do, and only together.

364
00:18:17,797 --> 00:18:19,497
That sounds familiar.

365
00:18:19,599 --> 00:18:21,632
         In honor of all
         they have done

366
00:18:21,734 --> 00:18:24,435
    and continue to do for
    the ponies of this town,

367
00:18:24,537 --> 00:18:27,438
     I would like to present
    the Cutie Mark Crusaders

368
00:18:27,540 --> 00:18:30,441
      with a three-handled
      key to the city!

369
00:18:30,543 --> 00:18:36,310
           [cheering]

370
00:18:36,418 --> 00:18:39,684
             [zoom]

371
00:18:39,886 --> 00:18:40,951
            [whoosh]

372
00:18:42,288 --> 00:18:44,222
               A full Wonderbolt
                salute?

373
00:18:44,424 --> 00:18:46,691
      Oh, I'm not sure you
     know just how important

374
00:18:46,793 --> 00:18:48,760
    Scootaloo and her friends
     are, little brother!

375
00:18:48,862 --> 00:18:50,562
  But you're about to find out!

376
00:18:51,764 --> 00:18:54,665
    The CMCs used their free
     time to set up a camp

377
00:18:54,767 --> 00:18:57,602
     to help us blank flanks
      find our cutie marks.

378
00:18:57,804 --> 00:19:00,771
   The Cutie Mark Crusaders
   see the best in everypony.

379
00:19:00,873 --> 00:19:03,274
    Even when that pony can't
      see it in themselves.

380
00:19:03,676 --> 00:19:05,977
       Well, I'll be a
     three-tailed bandicoot.

381
00:19:06,079 --> 00:19:08,613
   I had no idea how important
    Scoot's club was.

382
00:19:08,715 --> 00:19:11,649
        Oh, it's WAY more
        than just a club.

383
00:19:11,751 --> 00:19:13,117
 The CMCs have made a difference

384
00:19:13,219 --> 00:19:14,886
       for <i>everypony</i> here.

385
00:19:15,188 --> 00:19:18,590
    And not just ponies!
    They help everycreature.

386
00:19:19,192 --> 00:19:20,591
 Whether it's encouraging others

387
00:19:20,693 --> 00:19:22,326
        to discover their
         special talent.

388
00:19:22,428 --> 00:19:24,062
            [tapping]

389
00:19:24,164 --> 00:19:27,265
     Or inspiring them to do
     what's in their heart.

390
00:19:27,567 --> 00:19:29,333
       These three fillies
       offer the town

391
00:19:29,435 --> 00:19:31,069
  something no other pony can.

392
00:19:31,771 --> 00:19:33,704
         [train whistle]

393
00:19:39,980 --> 00:19:45,417
No way! After all that, you're
still gonna make her leave!?

394
00:19:46,019 --> 00:19:48,352
       We just want what's
       best for Scootaloo.

395
00:19:48,454 --> 00:19:51,825
   And until now...we thought
   we knew what that was.

396
00:19:53,227 --> 00:19:56,294
      [sigh] Turns out, you're
      just like us, Scoot.

397
00:19:56,596 --> 00:19:59,330
    You have an important
    job that only you can do.

398
00:19:59,632 --> 00:20:02,366
    You love it, and it
     helps all of Equestria.

399
00:20:04,337 --> 00:20:07,372
  Sometimes that means missing
  out on other things you love.

400
00:20:07,574 --> 00:20:09,941
      Like watching our
    daughter grow into a pony

401
00:20:10,043 --> 00:20:11,910
      we're very proud of.

402
00:20:12,112 --> 00:20:14,278
   Which is a long way to say:

403
00:20:14,380 --> 00:20:17,415
      Scoot, if you want to
      stay, we understand.

404
00:20:17,917 --> 00:20:18,683
             [gasp]

405
00:20:19,285 --> 00:20:24,022
         Really!? Thanks,
        Dad! Thanks, Mom!

406
00:20:24,124 --> 00:20:30,795
               ♪♪

407
00:20:30,897 --> 00:20:34,399
 Oh, sweetie. I'm just sorry
  we didn't realize it sooner.

408
00:20:34,501 --> 00:20:37,768
  Our work is our life's
  purpose. We could never quit.

409
00:20:37,870 --> 00:20:40,538
   So there's no way we could
   ask you to do the same.

410
00:20:42,108 --> 00:20:43,307
             Maybe you should've
             thought of that

411
00:20:43,409 --> 00:20:44,975
                 BEFORE you sold
                 the house.

412
00:20:46,045 --> 00:20:48,212
 Lofty, don't tease my brother!

413
00:20:48,314 --> 00:20:50,481
      We already have a
      solution worked out.

414
00:20:52,485 --> 00:20:55,653
  Since the CMCs make
  Ponyville such a nice place,

415
00:20:55,955 --> 00:20:57,488
   we've decided to move here.

416
00:20:57,690 --> 00:21:00,425
   You can live with us,
    Scootaloo. If you'd like.

417
00:21:01,027 --> 00:21:03,195
     That would be amazing!

418
00:21:04,197 --> 00:21:06,164
        Will you... still
         come and visit?

419
00:21:06,266 --> 00:21:07,498
           Of course!

420
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:09,800
     Rabid bugbears
     couldn't keep us away.

421
00:21:12,572 --> 00:21:15,373
      You get to stay here!
      You get to stay here!

422
00:21:15,575 --> 00:21:17,374
      You get to stay here!

423
00:21:17,676 --> 00:21:19,210
           [laughter]

424
00:21:19,312 --> 00:21:22,447
Uh, you ARE staying here, right?

425
00:21:22,749 --> 00:21:26,483
 Are you kidding? CMCs forever!

426
00:21:26,785 --> 00:21:28,652
             Woohoo!

427
00:21:28,754 --> 00:21:31,721
           [cheering]

